the project is required to be running in this way:
1. when boots Linux, this command is enabled to be run at the background: /usr/bin/project.sh, which starts the application after Postgres DB;
2. a service account sablabla has been created already which would be used to run the application;
3. if the application fails it should auto restarts, Bob sets restart interval 10 seconds on failure;
4. application events should be logged (auto-done in Linux), and his Linux boots in graphical mode.

set up these requirements in this file: /etc/systemd/system/projectblabla.service
[Unit]                                    //optional
Description=blabla for project blabla
Documentation=http://wiki.blabla      
After=postgresql.service                  //req 1

[Service]
ExecStart=/usr/bin/project.sh             //req 1
User=sablabla                             //req 2
Restart=on-failure                        //req 3
RestartSec=10                             //req 3

[Install]
WantedBy graphical.target                 //req 4

then run:
$ systemctl daemon-reload
$ systemctl start projectblabla.service

